Add hinting to xml/parse calls in uberjar and search.

The default implementation makes reflective calls here and triggers
warnings on post-java-8 versions:

WARNING: An illegal reflective access operation has occurred
WARNING: Illegal reflective access by clojure.lang.InjectedInvoker/0x000000084029a840 (file:/home/phil/.m2/repository/org/clojure/clojure/1.11.1/clojure-1.11.1.jar) to method com.sun.org.apache.xerces.internal.jaxp.SAXParserImpl.parse(org.xml.sax.InputSource,org.xml.sax.HandlerBase)
WARNING: Please consider reporting this to the maintainers of clojure.lang.InjectedInvoker/0x000000084029a840
WARNING: Use --illegal-access=warn to enable warnings of further illegal reflective access operations
WARNING: All illegal access operations will be denied in a future release

Release 2.9.9

Don't allow built-in templates to shadow remote templates.

We were stripping off the ns when we checked for built-in templates,
but now we use the full input for the built-in check.

Also add a new test for a template named default.
Merge branch 'domain-socket-repl' into main
Disable test-headless-socket until nrepl 1.0.0 is released

Hard-code names of built-in templates instead of querying classpath.

According to https://github.com/technomancy/leiningen/issues/2345 Java
9 broke the ability to query the classpath in the way we were doing
thru bultitude previously. Since Java 8 is in the minority now, we
will hardcode the template names instead of querying the classpath for
them.

This means that we can't show templates which come from plugins any
more, but it's better than showing nothing.

Fixes https://github.com/technomancy/leiningen/issues/2565

Fixes https://codeberg.org/leiningen/leiningen/issues/1

Do pedantic cycle detection based on strings, not dependency nodes.

Fixes https://github.com/technomancy/leiningen/issues/2798

This is caused by what seems like a bug in Aether's DependencyNode
implementation; most nodes will hash correctly such that

    (some #{node} parents)

works to do cycle detection, but certain ones in Netty's boringssl do
not hash correctly, so we have to convert them to strings before using
them for cycle detection purposes.

Add a simple "repl :headless :socket" test

This relies on an unreleased version of nrepl (likely to be 1.0.0).
It also doesn't completely clean up after itself because if nothing
else, the (server ...) future will be blocked forever on a promise.

Add "repl :headless :socket PATH" support

And match the configuration arrangments for the host, i.e. support
LEIN_REPL_SOCKET, :repl-options :socket, and an nrepl config :socket.
